"First chorus - bass in '2' - piano leaves lots of space"
"No sustain pedal used"
"LH jabs chords in more or less regular pattern just before '1' and just before '3'"
"'Surround' tones on A (the 9th) then finally on G (root) then D (5th)"
"On F7 - play from F chromatically up to tritone (B) back a m3rd (Ab) up a tritone (D) etc"
"Many melodic phrases are chord tones  'enclosed' with upper and lower neighbors"
"This is just an arbitary pattern - can be imposed on any chord -as long as it resolves smoothly "
"Typical Bill Evans-ish arpeggio like pattern on BbMaj 7 to EbMaj7"
"Simple melodic phrase can be enhanced by repeating each note in a regular rhythm"
"4 note pattern repeats moving down (more or less) in scale steps "
"Basic triad chord tones played rhythmically"
"Same melodic/rhythmic idea repeated diatonically  on another chord"
"Same rhythm begins the next chorus
column5: but seamlessly moves into other melodic ideas"
